@{FG Shine}Welcome to @{B}AmiChannel News@{UB}@{FG Text}

Hello and welcome to the 2nd issue of @{B}AmiChannel News@{UB}.

I  am  fed  up  with people making promises which can not be fulfilled. The last
straw  that  breaks  the camel's back has been the just held @{B}Amiwest@{UB}. The people
behind the show made a lot of announcemnent promoting their show. They failed to
fullfill most they promised.

They stated that all the staff of @{B}Amiga Inc.@{UB} would attend the show. Neither @{I}Jeff
Schindler @{UI} nor  Dr.  @{I}Allan  Havesome @{UI}attended the show. Even @{I}Petro, @{UI}who does not
service o@{B}Amiga@{UB} show, was not there.

They  stated  that  some  major announcement, no revealed before, would be made.
The  news  was  that the developer machine is no longer called @{B}"OS 4.0"@{UB} and that
it will not have @{B}Windows@{UB} on it. Great news!

They  stated  that  the  IRC  logs  from the show would be posted in a given WEB
pages. There is nothing in their WEB pages.

I  think that it is enough. My mother told me that never promise anything if you
don't  know  it  is  possible  to  fulfill.  I blocked the release of this issue
waiting for some important news which never was planned to announce.

Anyway,  the  great  news  is  that  the  jewel  of @{B}Phase 5@{UB} is now shipping. The
eagerly  awaited  @{B}Cybervision PPC@{UB} is now avalaible. If you have a @{B}PPC@{UB} card, this
graphic card is a must.

Remember to visit the @{B}SAUG@{UB} website, which is located in:

	@{B}http://www.saug.com/sau/@{UB}                    (California, USA)

or you can visit its mirrors located in:

	@{B}http://soporte.databasedm.es/amiga/sau/@{UB}     (Spain)

And if you want to contribute to this effort, you can send your articles to:

	@{I}angel@saug.org @{UI}

Thanks for reading and I hope you enjoy this issue.

===============================================================================
@{I}Angel Alvarez Díaz @{UI} - @{I}angel@saug.org @{UI}
Moderator of the mailing list @{B}SAU-Games@{UB}
Responsible of the News Departament of @{B}S.A.U.@{UB} and @{B}Amiga Channel@{UB}.
Editor of the e-magazine called @{B}AmiChannel News@{UB}.
