June 1st 1998

Continuing the @{B}Amiga@{UB} future with @{B}DES II-2@{UB} and new clients

The  @{B}Amiga RC5 Team@{UB} effort is proud to announce new and improved @{B}PowerPC@{UB} clients
(as well as @{B}68k@{UB}) for the ongoing @{B}RSA Secret Key@{UB} challenges, participating in the
@{B}Distributed Net/Bovine RC5-64@{UB} and the upcoming @{B}DES II-2@{UB} contests.

With  the announcement of the roadmap to the next generation @{B}Amiga@{UB} by @{B}Amiga Inc.@{UB}
we  feel  the  @{B}Amiga@{UB}  has  a  clear  future,  destined to be at the forefront of
alternative,  perhaps  even  mainstream  computing again. With this knowledge in
hand  our  effort  focuses  on exposure for the @{B}Amiga@{UB} and it's user community by
competing  at  the  very  top  of  above  mentioned challenges, currently ranked
seventh  out  of  thousands of competing teams, amongst others in hot pursuit of
the @{B}Win32@{UB}/@{B}Windows@{UB} team.

Again  many  thanks  must  go to @{I}Stefan 'Blast' Smietanowski @{UI}for the programming
efforts  spent  to improve the clients, @{I}Steve Krueger @{UI}for compiler help and many
others, amongst which of course those already contributing CPU power.

We ask all of you who own an @{B}Amiga@{UB} or support the @{B}Amiga@{UB} in spirit to join us now
for  the  @{B}DES  II-2@{UB}  challenge  starting on July 13th, the short interim project
estimated  to  last  around  ten  days,  intended to show the weakness of 56 bit
encryption. An award of in total US $10,000 is connected to this effort, part of
which could go to the @{B}Amiga@{UB} team and the individual finding the key. Our chances
are  indeed  excellent with over 1000 contributing members governing nearly 2000
machines in total.

The  @{B}Amiga  RC5  Team@{UB}  effort is also providing a mailinglist as a forum for the
discussion on above topics and the effort in general.

For  additional info on how to participate and more in depth explanation, please
visit the @{B}Amiga RC5 Team@{UB} effort homepage at: @{B}http://www.cistron.nl/~ttavoly/rc5@{UB}

Sincerely,

@{B}Amiga RC5 Team@{UB} effort coordinator
@{I}Thomas Tavoly @{UI}- @{I}rc5@amiga.cistron.nl @{UI}
