@node not12 "EYELIGHT ANNOUNCES A NEW AGE IN 3D COMPUTER GRAPHICS"

@{FG Shine}@{B}EYELIGHT@{UB} ANNOUNCES A NEW AGE IN 3D COMPUTER GRAPHICS@{FG Text}
¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯
@{FG Fill}DATE: 1998/06/15@{FG Text}

@{I}What is @{B}"'Mage." @{UB}? @{UI}

@{B}"'Mage."@{UB} is a complete, modular 3D graphics package that allows to easily model,
animate and render at blazing speed on @{B}Risc @{UB}based computers and workstations.

@{I}Why @{B}Risc @{UB}-only? @{UI}

Because  @{B}Risc@{UB} architecture is perfectly suited to 3D computer graphics. Both the
@{B}PowerPC@{UB}  and  @{B}Mips  R5K@{UB}  architectures provide the invaluable MACC (Multiply and
Accumulate)  all-in-one  instructions  that  easily account for 80% of processor
operations during preview or rendering.

@{I}Is @{B}"'Mage." Tornado3D @{UB}with another name? @{UI}

No,  it  is an entirely different product, that builds on the expertise acquired
developing  @{B}Tornado3D@{UB}.  @{B}"'Mage."@{UB}  however  is  even  more  oriented  towards the
professional  market  and  platform  independance.  @{B}"'Mage."@{UB}  targets the TV and
hi-end video-game special effects production houses.

@{I}Does this mean @{B}Tornado3D @{UB}is dead? Are you leaving the @{B}Amiga @{UB}? @{UI}

No,  not  at  all.  @{B}Tornado3D@{UB}  development  continues, we are already working to
define  @{B}V3.0@{UB}  features.  @{B}"'Mage."@{UB} already runs on @{B}PPC Amiga@{UB}s and will presumably
run  on  "Future  @{B}Amiga@{UB}s".  @{B}Tornado3D@{UB}  and  @{B}"'Mage."@{UB} are two different products,
managed  by  different development teams and oriented towards different markets.
What's  more,  @{B}"'Mage."@{UB}'s  100%  @{B}PowerPC@{UB}  technology  and industry standard user
interface are likely to be integrated into future releases of @{B}Tornado3D@{UB} as well.

@{I}How much does @{B}"'Mage." @{UB}cost? When will it be available? @{UI}

@{B}"'Mage."@{UB}  is  tentatively  priced  at 1299,00 USD for first promotional release.
This  first  release  distribution is scheduled to begin in october 1998, with a
massive marketing campaign to follow in first quarter 1999.

@{I}Will there be some kind of cross-grade from @{B}Tornado3D @{UB}to @{B}"'Mage." @{UB}? @{UI}

Yes,  @{B}Tornado3D@{UB}  users  will  be entitled to cross-grade to @{B}"'Mage."@{UB} should they
want to. As per @{B}Eyelight@{UB}'s policy, long time @{B}Tornado3D@{UB} users will be entitled to
more  convenient  upgrades.  "First  Buyers" (users that bought @{B}T3D@{UB} before @{B}T3D@{UB}'s
DEMO  version  was  released)  will  even be able to cross-grade to @{B}"'Mage."@{UB} for
free.

@{I}Any hint about @{B}"'Mage."'s @{UB}features? Do @{B}Tornado3D's @{UB}features apply? @{UI}

@{B}Tornado3D@{UB}  and  @{B}"'Mage."@{UB}  share  some features, but they are different products.
Where  @{B}Tornado3D@{UB}  is  a "swiss army knife" of 3D graphics, offering something to
everyone,  @{B}"'Mage."@{UB}  has  a  smaller and more specialized feature set. A new web
site  devoted  to  @{B}"'Mage."@{UB} is under construction and will hold all the @{B}"'Mage."@{UB}
specific issues.

@{I}Supported platforms @{UI}

@{B}Amiga@{UB}
@{B}PowerPC@{UB}-based @{B}Amiga@{UB} (@{B}"'Mage."@{UB} runs 100% @{B}PowerPC@{UB} native)
3D accelerated 15bit+ graphics card
