@node not15 "YAMAHA KEEP THE SUPPORT FOR AMIGA COMPUTERS"

@{FG Shine}@{B}YAMAHA@{UB} KEEP THE SUPPORT FOR @{B}AMIGA@{UB} COMPUTERS@{FG Text}
¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯
@{FG Fill}DATE: 1998/06/15@{FG Text}

SAN  JOSE,  Calif.--The new generation @{B}Yamaha CRW2216E@{UB} with 2X write, 2X rewrite
and  16X  read  speeds  and the @{B}CRW4216S@{UB} with 4X write, 2X rewrite, and 16X read
will be shown at @{B}PC Expo@{UB} in New York in the @{B}Yamaha Systems Technology Inc.@{UB} Booth
No. 4587.

The  two  new drives represent the fastest read speeds of any CD-RW drive on the
market,  and  boast  the  same  high  reliability of the previous members of the
award-winning  @{B}Yamaha  Multifunction  CD-RW@{UB}  drives.  Both are available for the
retail and OEM markets.

The  @{B}CRW2216E@{UB}  will be shown with an @{B}ATAPI@{UB} (@{B}IDE@{UB}) interface; the @{B}CRW4216S@{UB} will be
shown  with  a  @{B}SCSI@{UB}  interface.  (Both  will  be  available  later,  with  both
interfaces).  All  of  the  features of the earlier CD-RW drives from @{B}Yamaha@{UB} are
incorporated as well, in the same half-height, 5-1/4 inch space.

In  a  related  announcement,  @{B}Yamaha  Japan@{UB}  has  completed  a  higher capacity
production  line for the CD-RW products, to meet the ever-growing demands of the
CD-RW drive marketplace. The new production line is up and running.

@{I}"These  announcements  reflect @{B}Yamaha's @{UB}continuing response to the needs of the 
market," @{UI} said  @{I}Dean  Quarnstrom, @{UI}CDR Sales Manager for the @{B}Yamaha@{UB} CD-RW product
line.  @{I}"The  consumer looking for a lower priced CD-RW with 2X write speed will 
love the high quality and fast read speed of the @{B}CRW2216E. @{UB}The high end market, 
which  traditionally  wants more speed in their write function, will choose the 
@{B}CRW4216S. @{UB}This new product pair spans the spectrum of user needs, with many new 
enhancements." @{UI}

The  @{B}CRW4216S@{UB} writing speed, using standard CD-R media is 4X normal speed. Using
CD-RW  media,  rewriting  speed  is  2X.  Both  can be read at 16X. The @{B}CRW2216E@{UB}
writing  speed  is  2X normal speed with 2X rewrite and 16X read speeds. The new
drives conform to standard Orange Book Part II and Part III.

The  CDs  produced  by  the  CDR  function of the drives can be read on ordinary
CD-ROM  drives,  CDR  drives and Multi-Read CD/DVD drives. Media produced by the
CD-RW function of the two new drives can be read on Multi-Read CD/DVD drives.

@{I}@{B}CRW2216 @{UB}and @{B}CRW4216 @{UB}Features @{UI}

The new @{B}CRW2216@{UB} and @{B}CRW4216@{UB} include all of the features of the previous CD-R and
CD-RW  drives,  as  well  as  the  new,  advanced  16X read speed. Some of these
features include:

   o 2MB data buffer on the @{B}CRW4216@{UB} to eliminate buffer underrun.
   o 1MB data buffer on the @{B}CRW2216@{UB} to eliminate buffer underrun.
   o @{B}RapidLinked(TM) Packet Writing@{UB} for higher performance data transfer.
   o @{B}SCSI@{UB} models support synchronous data transfer for high-end duplication.
   o Flash ROM for simple downloading of firmware upgrades.
   o Packet    writing,    track-at-once,    disc-at-once/session-at-once    and
     multisession modes.
   o Eight  standard  formats  supported  including  CD-Digital  Audio,  CD-ROM,
     CD-ROMXA  (both  Photo  and  Video  CD), CD-I, CD-G (karaoke), CD-Extra and
     Video CD.
   o Running Optimum Power Control (ROPC) for maximized media writing integrity.
   o Support  of all major platforms including @{B}Windows '95@{UB}, @{B}Windows '98@{UB}, @{B}Windows
     NT@{UB},  @{B}OS2@{UB},  @{B}UNIX@{UB},  @{B}Sun@{UB},  @{B}Macintosh@{UB}, @{B}Novell@{UB}, @{B}NLS@{UB}, @{B}HP9000@{UB}, @{B}DOS@{UB}, @{B}DEC@{UB}, @{B}Amiga@{UB} and
     @{B}AIX@{UB}.

@{I}Price and Availability @{UI}

Volume  shipments  of  the  @{B}Yamaha  CRW2216E@{UB}  will  begin in August 1998. Volume
shipments  of  the @{B}Yamaha CRW4216S@{UB} will begin in September 1998. Pricing has not
been determined.

@{B}Yamaha@{UB} CD-RW drives are available through distributors: @{B}Law Cypress Distributing
Company@{UB}, @{B}Optical Laser@{UB}, @{B}Consan Storage Solutions@{UB}, @{B}Advanced Optical Distribution@{UB},
@{B}Applied  Storage  Products@{UB}  and @{B}Yamaha of Canada@{UB}. A retail version, bundled with
software  is  available  through  @{B}Yamaha  Corp.  of  America@{UB},  Consumer Products
Division.

@{B}Yamaha  Systems Technology Inc.@{UB} was founded to manufacture and market integrated
circuits,  board  level  products and complete systems to OEMs and Distributors.
The   product  line  includes  multimedia  audio,  graphics  and  communications
products,  as  well  as  custom  and semicustom ASICs, and CD Recorder products.
@{B}http://www.yamahayst.com@{UB}
