@node not23 "CLOANTO RELEASES PP 6.4 AS FREE & ANNOUNCES DEVELOPMENT OF VERSION 8"

@{FG Shine}@{B}CLOANTO RELEASES@{UB} @{B}PP 6.4@{UB} AS FREE & ANNOUNCES DEVELOPMENT OF VERSION @{B}8@{UB}@{FG Text}
¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯
@{FG Fill}DATE: 1998/06/26@{FG Text}

In  the  evolution  of  @{B}Personal  Paint@{UB},  which has become the leading title for
editing  palette-based  graphics,  version  @{B}6.4@{UB}  represents  a  milestone in new
features,  reliability,  diffusion  and new code written. In hindsight, it might
have  deserved  a  version number of @{B}"7"@{UB} (just as the features introduced in the
latest  version  might have justified an @{B}"8"@{UB} release, instead of the more humble
@{B}7.1@{UB}).  The  particular  release  of  @{B}Personal Paint 6.4@{UB} now on Aminet (@{B}biz/cloan@{UB}
directory,        @{B}PPaint64.lha@{UB}       archive,       easy       access       from
@{B}http://www.cloanto.com/amiga/download.html@{UB})  is  little more than 18 months old,
and includes support for anim-brushes and @{B}ARexx@{UB}, which were not supported by the
first @{B}6.4@{UB} release (also bundled with some @{B}Amiga@{UB} computers).

With  few  exceptions, such as the lack of full documentation and no support for
file  formats  such  as @{B}GIF@{UB} (which is included only with the commercial package,
under  license  of  @{B}Unisys  Corporation@{UB}),  this  is  the  full retail version of
@{B}Personal  Paint 6.4@{UB}, including 20 different user interface languages. Additional
information  on  the  distribution  is contained in the archive, as is a special
upgrade  offer  to the latest version @{B}7.1@{UB}. The version of @{B}Personal Paint 6.4@{UB} now
released  for  free  download  is  not  a  demonstration  version,  but is fully
functional, and may be used without limitations for productive applications.

@{B}Personal  Paint  7.1@{UB} remains the latest version, while we are working on version
@{B}8@{UB},  which  however is not expected to be ready at least until the second half of
1999.  @{B}Personal  Paint  8@{UB}  requires a major re-write to support features such as
true  color,  layers, and advanced animation functionality. At the same time, it
is  now very important that the new code be written in a portable style, because
it is still unknown what the new @{B}Amiga OS@{UB} will look like, other than it will not
be the @{B}Amiga@{UB} that we are used to. Suggestions regarding the features of @{B}Personal
Paint  8@{UB}  are  very  welcome,  and  can be addressed to @{I}suggestions@cloanto.com @{UI}
(preferably containing @{B}"Personal Paint 8"@{UB} in the message title).

For additional information, please refer to the @{B}Amiga@{UB} section of the @{B}Cloanto@{UB} web
site at @{B}http://www.cloanto.com/amiga/@{UB}
