@node not25 "AA+ CHIP SET"

@{FG Shine}@{B}AA+@{UB} CHIP SET@{FG Text}
¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯
@{FG Fill}DATE: 1998/06/30@{FG Text}

@{B}Access Innovation Ltd@{UB} are working on a next generation @{B}AGA@{UB} chip set, called @{B}AA+@{UB},
which offers higher levels of performance, features and integration.

The  chip  set  is  based around a totally new full 32-bit functional core, this
then  has a 16-bit @{B}AGA@{UB} hardware register emulation wrapped around it. The 32-bit
core,  using  modern memory access techniques can achieve 20-times the bandwidth
of  the  original  @{B}AGA@{UB}  chip  memory.  The  effect of improved memory access and
buffering  is  that @{B}DMA@{UB} access for the video display takes significantly less of
the  available bandwidth and is less time critical, this allows a @{B}Unified Memory
Architecture@{UB}  (@{B}UMA@{UB})  to  be  used  without  causing  significant  conflicts with
processor  operation.  When  accessing the original @{B}Blitter@{UB} the 16-bit registers
are translated to 32-bit operations, using burst memory access at up to 20-times
the speed of the original @{B}Blitter@{UB}.

@{I}FEATURE @{UI}

   o Processor   interface  (@{B}68020@{UB},  @{B}68030@{UB},  @{B}68040@{UB},  @{B}ColdFire  5102@{UB}  or  @{B}PowerPC@{UB}
     options).
   o Address decoding for @{B}ROM@{UB}, @{B}RTC@{UB}, @{B}RAM@{UB}, etc.
   o @{B}DRAM@{UB} controller for @{B}SIMM@{UB}'s/@{B}DIMM@{UB}'s.
   o @{B}PCI@{UB} bus controller.
   o @{B}AGA@{UB} compatible.
   o Supports   additional   chunky   mode  displays  while  retaining  backward
     compatibility  with  @{B}WB3.1@{UB}  (chunky  display  works  using  @{B}CyberGraphics@{UB} /
     @{B}Picasso96@{UB}).
   o Resolutions up to 1024x768x16-bit.
   o 16-bit sound.
   o @{B}UMA@{UB} for lowest memory sub-system costs.
   o @{B}Blitter@{UB} up to 20-times faster.
   o High-density floppy drive support.
   o @{B}CIA@{UB}'s (optionally using external buffers to reduce @{B}ASIC@{UB} pin count).
   o @{B}DMA@{UB} engine.
   o Interface  to  a  SuperIO chip to allow low cost serial, parallel, @{B}UDMA IDE@{UB}
     and @{B}USB@{UB} to be implemented off chip.

It  is  intended  that  features  such  as  @{B}Firewire@{UB},  modems  and  networks  be
implemented using a plug-in @{B}PCI@{UB} card or integrated @{B}PCI@{UB} chip solution.
