@node not38 "THE CYBERVISION PPC GRAPHIC CARD IS NOW AVALAIBLE"

@{FG Shine}THE @{B}CYBERVISION PPC@{UB} GRAPHIC CARD IS NOW AVALAIBLE@{FG Text}
¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯
@{FG Fill}DATE: 1998/07/15@{FG Text}

@{B}CyberVisionPPC@{UB}  - A high-end graphic card for the @{B}Cyberstorm PPC@{UB} / @{B}Blizzard 2604
Power Board@{UB}

The  @{B}CyberVisionPPC@{UB} is a high-performance graphic card which can be installed on
the   expansion   slot   of  the  @{B}PowerPC604e@{UB}-based  @{B}PowerUp@{UB}  accelerators,  the
@{B}Cyberstorm  PPC@{UB}  and  the @{B}Blizzard 2604 Power Board@{UB}. Especially for the @{B}Blizzard
2604@{UB}  the  use of the @{B}CyberVisionPPC@{UB} is highly recommended as the slow access to
the  @{B}ECS@{UB}  chip  memory  or @{B}Zorro-II@{UB}-based graphics boards in the @{B}A1500@{UB}/@{B}A2000@{UB} may
limit  the  system  performance in applications with lots of graphic output. The
performance of the @{B}CyberVisionPPC@{UB} benefits from the high data bandwidth achieved
by  the use of the direct connection to the processor bus by use of the graphics
direct  connector  which  incredibly  speeds  up  for  example  3D rendering and
display.

Not  only the ultra-fast access of the processor into the video memory, but also
the  internal  speed  and  functionality  of  the  @{B}CyberVisionPPC@{UB} will provide a
breathtaking  performance.  The  @{B}CyberVisionPPC@{UB}  is  equipped  with the powerful
@{B}PERMEDIA2@{UB}  graphics  controller, which provides an outstanding 3D performance of
up  to  80  million  textured  3D  pixels  per second, with hardware-accelerated
rendering  functions such as z-buffering, gouraud-shading, fogging, blending and
anti-aliasing.  As  the  design  of  the  @{B}PERMEDIA2@{UB} hardware suits perfectly for
@{B}OpenGL@{UB}   implementations,   it's   3D   performance   can  support  the  @{B}CyberGL@{UB}
functionality  of  @{B}CyberGraphX  V3  Native@{UB}  which  comes  along with the @{B}PowerUp@{UB}
boards.   In  combination  with  the  high  floating-point  performance  of  the
@{B}PowerPC604e@{UB}   processor   a   breathtaking   performance   in   professional  3D
applications   can   be  achieved  by  this  implementation.  Additionally,  the
@{B}PERMEDIA2@{UB}  processor  supports  functions  like  color  space conversion, chroma
keying  and XY-scaling which will be used by the software MPEG decoding routines
of @{B}CyberGraphX V3 Native@{UB}.

Memory  on the @{B}CyberVisionPPC@{UB} is 64 bit wide SGRAM with data throuput upto 800MB
per  second  which results on use of the ultra fast RAMDAC in the possibility to
display  upto 1280x1024 in true color at 85 Hz screen refresh rate and 1600x1200
in  true color at 60 Hz or high color at 85 Hz. The board will be delivered with
4 MB or 8 MB display memory.
