@node rc5 "THE AMIGA RC5 TEAM EFFORT NEWS"

@{FG Shine}THE @{B}AMIGA RC5 TEAM@{UB} EFFORT NEWS@{FG Text}
¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯
The following is from the @{B}Amiga RC5 Team@{UB} effort homepage at:
	@{B}http://www.cistron.nl/~ttavoly/rc5/@{UB}

@{I}01-Jun-98 @{UI}

First  reports  on  new clients are in, most are positive (increase in @{B}PPC@{UB} speed
for  example,  more  solid  for  most  etc.), though a couple of small bugs were
found:  when running with @{I}-runoffline, @{UI}and running out of blocks client crashes.
This  and  anything  else  found  will be fixed shortly, stay tuned. It is still
advisable to upgrade, even if you had no trouble before.

@{I}02-Jun-98 @{UI}

A  note  to  people for whom the new clients crash: make absolutely sure you are
not  using  old buffers, especially from clients with versions @{B}2.6xxx@{UB}. These are
not  compatible,  flush  with  old  client first and delete leftover files, then
fetch new ones and run new client on that.

@{I}19-Jun-98 @{UI}

A  reminder:  If  you need any quick help with clients, the main IRC channel for
th e @{B}RC5@{UB} effort is @{B}#distributed@{UB} on @{B}EFnet@{UB}. Also available are @{B}#AmigaRC5@{UB} on @{B}IRCnet@{UB}
(recently established, @{I}'Spookie' @{UI}will try to keep it open). And of course @{B}#amiga@{UB}
on @{B}ANet@{UB} @{I}('aTmosh'). @{UI}

@{I}27-Jun-98 @{UI}

Only  300  thousand  blocks  separate  us from the @{B}Win32@{UB} team now, we might just
catch   them  before  @{B}DES  II-2@{UB}  starts.  New  @{B}2.7100@{UB}  clients  are  already  in
development,  hopefully  they  will  be  ready  for @{B}DES II-2@{UB}. Note that @{B}DES II-2@{UB}
starts  13th July and is estimated to run less than 10 days, keep an eye on this
section for announcement of the new clients. In any case you should upgrade to a
@{B}DES@{UB}  capable client now if you haven't already (preferably the already available
@{B}2.7021.405@{UB}  one,  since  that  one  will  automatically  switch  to  @{B}DES II-2@{UB} if
configured right).
